{"lemma":"أَبْيَضِ","slug":"أَبْيَضِ","root":"ب.#.ض","root_slug":"ب-_-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-_-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَبْيَض","root":"بيض","pos":"N","occurrence_count":8},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n45","n3628","n3637"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8E%D8%B6%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"white"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ب ي ض (b y ḍ)."},"ipa":["/ʔab.jadˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n45","headword_ar":"اُبَيِّضٌ","root":"AbD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibaADN","text_ar":"اـِبَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3628","headword_ar":"ابيضّ","root":"byD","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, Msb, K,) and, by poetic license,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiboyaDaD~a","text_ar":"اِبْيَضَضَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [of which see an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafaDa","text_ar":"خَفَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and see also 9 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hw","text_ar":"حو"},{"kind":"text","text":",] (M, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiboyiDaADN","text_ar":"اِبْيِضَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, white;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisowad~a","text_ar":"اِسْوَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbyAD~","text_ar":"ابياضّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AiboyiyDaADN","text_ar":"اِبْيِيضَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";. (S;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AisowaAd~a","text_ar":"اِسْوَادَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abaADa","text_ar":"اَبَاضَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": which ↓ last also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(herbage or pasture)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became white, and dried up."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, TA.) [You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AbyD~ wajohuhu","text_ar":"ابيضّ وَجْهُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", lit.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His face became white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his face became expressive of joy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerfulness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he became joyful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheerful:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his character became cleared;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his honesty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, became manifested:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see 2.]"}],"source_refs":["S","M","Msb","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n3637","headword_ar":"اَبْيَضُ","root":"byD","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asowadu","text_ar":"اَسْوَدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) fem."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyDN","text_ar":"بِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"buyoDN","text_ar":"بُيْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) the damm being converted into kesr in order that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":"may remain unchanged, (S, K,) [i. e.] to suit the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Y","text_ar":"ى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) In the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEoTiniY A^aboyaD~aho","text_ar":"اَعْطِنِى اَبْيَضَّهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Sb, as used by some of the Arabs, meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaDa","text_ar":"اَبْيَضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Give thou to me a white one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"is subjoined as it is in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hun~aho","text_ar":"هُنَّهْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hun~a","text_ar":"هُنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":"is doubled because the letter of declinability cannot have"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"subjoined to it; wherefore the letter of declinability is the first"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the second is the augmentative, and for this reason it has subjoined to it the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":"whereof the purpose is to render plainly perceivable the vowel [which is necessarily added after the doubled"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"D","text_ar":"ض"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: Aboo-'Alee says, [app. of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h","text_ar":"ه"},{"kind":"text","text":",] that it should properly have neither fet-h nor any vowel. (M.) ―         -b2-  Applied to a man &c., it was sometimes used to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White in complexion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but in this sense they generally used the epithet"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaru","text_ar":"اَحْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAth, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmr","text_ar":"حمر"},{"kind":"text","text":".) They also said,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN A^aboyaDu Alwajohi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ اَبْيَضُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnapu bayoDaA='u Alwajohi","text_ar":"فُلَانَةُ بَيْضَا=ءُ الوَجْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a man,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such a woman, is clear, in face, from freckles or the like, and unseemly blackness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) And they used"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyDaAnN","text_ar":"بِيضَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaDu","text_ar":"اَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) in the contr. of the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suwdaAnN","text_ar":"سُودَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) [i. e. as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whites,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] applied to men: (S:) though they applied the appellation"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw AlbayoDaA='i","text_ar":"اَبُو البَيْضَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Abyssinian:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewr","text_ar":"عور"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the negro:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abuw Aljawoni","text_ar":"اَبُو الجَوْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"to the white man. (ISk.) But accord. to Th,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaDu","text_ar":"اَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man signifies only (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pure; free from faults:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hmr","text_ar":"حمر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or, so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unsullied in honour, nobility,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"estimation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free from faults;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"generous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a woman. (Az.) [In the lexicons, however, (see, for ex., among countless other instances, an explanation of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baD~apN","text_ar":"بَضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the S,) and in other post-classical works, it is generally used, when thus applied, in its proper sense, of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"White;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fair in complexion."},{"kind":"text","text":"] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"katiybapN bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"كَتِيبَةٌ بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An army,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a portion thereof, upon which the whiteness of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arms or armour of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"iron is apparent."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"alone, [as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A piece of paper"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"without writing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 311.) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aboyaDu","text_ar":"الاَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sword:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) because of its whiteness: (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyDN","text_ar":"بِيضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Silver:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K:) because of its whiteness: like as gold is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aHomaru","text_ar":"الاَحْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[because of its redness]. (TA.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The saliva"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rDAb","text_ar":"رضاب"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the mouth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 348.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain star in the margin of the milky way."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbayoDaA='u","text_ar":"البَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun:"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of its whiteness. (M.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Waste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uncultivated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uninhabited, land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, * TA: [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljirAbu","text_ar":"الجِرابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is erroneously put for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxaraAbu","text_ar":"الخَرَابُ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awodaA='u","text_ar":"السَّوْدَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": because dead lands are white; and when planted, become black and green. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDapN","text_ar":"بَيْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", near the end. ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Wheat:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~amoraA='u","text_ar":"السَّمْرَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fresh"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sulot","text_ar":"سُلْت"},{"kind":"text","text":". (El-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":284},{"kind":"text","text":"Khattábee, K.) ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain kind of wood; that which is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHawaru","text_ar":"الحَوَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hwr","text_ar":"حور"},{"kind":"text","text":":) because of its whiteness. (TA in that art.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawarN","text_ar":"حَوَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The cooking-pot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^um~u bayoDaA='a","text_ar":"اُمُّ بَيْضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (AA, K.) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The snare with which one catches game."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aboyaDaAni","text_ar":"الاَبْيَضَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Milk and water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, M, A, K.) A poet says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wamaA liYa A_il~aA AlA^aboyaDayoni $araAbu"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And I have not any beverage except milk and water"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (ISk, S, M.) ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bread and water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat and water:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fat and milk."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AO, K.) ―         -b18-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fat and youthfulness"},{"kind":"text","text":"(AZ, IAar, M, A, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba A^aboyaDaAhu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ اَبْيَضَاهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His fat and youthfulness departed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b19-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA raA^ayotuhu","text_ar":"مَا رَاَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu*o A^aboyaDaAni","text_ar":"مُذْ اَبْيَضَانِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I have not seen him for,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"during, two days:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, M, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two months."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ks, M, K.) ―         -b20-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~aAmu AlbiyDi","text_ar":"اَيَّامُ البِيضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) or simply"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlbiyDu","text_ar":"البِيضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ay~aAmu All~ayaAliY AlbiyDi","text_ar":"اَيَّامُ اللَّيَالِى البِيضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The days of the white nights;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the days of the thirteenth and fourteenth and fifteenth nights of the month;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K;) so called because they are lighted by the moon throughout: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the twelfth and thirteenth and fourteenth nights:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) but this is of weak authority, and extr.: the former is the correct explanation: (MF, TA:) you should not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ay~aAmu AlbiyDu","text_ar":"الاَيَّامُ البِيضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ibn-El-Jawá- leekee, IB, K:) yet thus it is in most relations of a trad. in which it occurs; and some argue for it; and the author of the K has himself explained"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^awaADiHu","text_ar":"الاَوَاضِحُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ay~aAmu AlbiyDu","text_ar":"الاَيَّامُ البِيضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b21-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sanapN bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"سَنَةٌ بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A year"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of scarcity of herbage,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is a mean between that which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ahobaA='","text_ar":"شَهْبَا=ء"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and that which is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoraA='","text_ar":"حَمْرَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$hb","text_ar":"شهب"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b22-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kalaAmN","text_ar":"كَلَامٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboyaDu","text_ar":"اَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Language expounded"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"explained."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b23-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kal~amotuhu famaA rad~a EalaY~a sawodaA='a walaA bayoDaA='a","text_ar":"كَلَّمْتُهُ فَمَا رَدَّ عَلَىَّ سَوْدَا=ءَ وَلَا بَيْضَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I spoke to him, and he did not return to me a bad word nor a good one."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b24-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadN bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"يَدٌ بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A demonstrating,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"demonstrated, argument, plea, allegation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evidence."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b25-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A favour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefit, for which one is not reproached;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is conferred without its being asked."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadN","text_ar":"يَدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b26-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawotu AlA^aboyaDu","text_ar":"المَوْتُ الاَبْيَضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Sudden death;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is not preceded by disease which alters the complexion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"death without the repentance, and the prayer for forgiveness, and the accomplishment of necessary duties, usual with him who is not taken unawares;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bay~aDa","text_ar":"بَيَّضَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying “ he emptied ” a vessel: so says Sgh: opposed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almawotu AlA^aHomaru","text_ar":"المَوْتُ الاَحْمَرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is slaughter. (TA.) ―         -b27-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDaA='u","text_ar":"بَيْضَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A calamity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"misfortune:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sgh, K:) app. as a term of good omen; like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saliymN","text_ar":"سَلِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to one who is stung by a scorpion or bitten by a serpent. (TA.) ―         -b28-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDaA='u AlqayoZi","text_ar":"بَيْضَا=ءُ القَيْظِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayoDapN","text_ar":"بَيْضَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last sentence but one.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA A^aboyaDu mino ka*aA","text_ar":"هٰذَا اَبْيَضُ مِنْ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bayaADN","text_ar":"بَيَاضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","S","K","TA","A","As","M","Fr","Ks","Mgh","MF","Sgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}